<subSubSection id="DD063C4FCE480AA58AC84B271485C5AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C3316B62B5BAB87977E793C70F372514" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B7165DCA2DB92B6685671007EFFC95D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis id="4C195C1128A2C8381DA37E2969D6E415" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Male</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="88652BDE13F84BAF161D552A8F1FD285" captionStart="Figures 1â8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Xystromutilla bucki 1 - 6 male: 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view 3 right wings 4 genitalia, dorsal view 5 genitalia, ventral view 6 penis valve, lateral view 7, 8 female: 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1011.60944.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/498659" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">1-6</figureCitation>
). This species can be recognized by its unique coloration, wherein the meso-metathorax, propodeum and first metasomal segment are orange-red; wings subhyaline. The following morphological characters are also useful for diagnosis: head with simple setae; mandible ventrally with a strong basal tooth; sternum 1 without a spine; hypopygium posterior margin with a small denticle medially; paramere almost straight and cuspis finger-shaped. Other described males of 
<taxonomicName id="ECD7FF9F6B8990E9E9A6C66380D624FD" authority="AndrÃ©, 1905" authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Xystromutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xystromutilla" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5FBE086D6611C621EA874F663E2C7990" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Xystromutilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have black integument, fore wings partly or totally fuscous, sternum 1 with a basal spine, hypopygium with medial spine on the apical margin, paramere lyre-shaped and cuspis elongate spoon-shaped. These morphological characters are not present in males of 
<taxonomicName id="AC9BD9719D7478B757D393478989D1C6" genus="X." lsidName="X. bucki" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" rank="species" species="bucki">
<emphasis id="86E5856437966349B99F84E1AACEC228" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">X. bucki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis id="BCED4318A93066A55CEC78694E3F2157" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Female</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="E8A4F5625DA95C7B848BDA4DB84E4044" captionStart="Figures 1â8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Xystromutilla bucki 1 - 6 male: 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view 3 right wings 4 genitalia, dorsal view 5 genitalia, ventral view 6 penis valve, lateral view 7, 8 female: 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1011.60944.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/498659" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="8C02D4165836F23CBFB813D0A0293623" captionStart="Figures 1â8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Xystromutilla bucki 1 - 6 male: 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view 3 right wings 4 genitalia, dorsal view 5 genitalia, ventral view 6 penis valve, lateral view 7, 8 female: 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1011.60944.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/498659" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">8</figureCitation>
). Head, pronotum and metasomal segment 1 orange-red, rest of metasoma black; head with simple setae only; humeral angles of pronotum rounded, not carinate; integument of basal half of tergum 2 without carinae.
</paragraph>
